title: TCPR Link
body:
As a leading cause of early death, cardiovascular diseases kill nearly 18 million people every year, accounting for 31% of all global deaths. One third of these deaths are caused by sudden cardiac arrest, a condition where the heart stops pumping blood.

The odds of surviving from out-of-hospital cardiac arrest without help are very slim. However, if bystanders are present and able to perform good CPR until the ambulance arrives, the chance of survival will increase significantly. 
TCPR Link is a system that helps CPR volunteers give good CPR to victims of cardiac arrest, by working together with the dispatcher.

title: Course summary
body:
Congratulations - training completed!

During this course you have learned how novel technology can establish great collaboration between myResponder and dispatcher in a cardiac arrest, and help provide quality CPR to the patient.
You can help save a life!
